    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Flawed Missiles</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stephen W Worrel letter comments on July 15 article on antiballistic missile test failure</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>So long as we are threatened by only a few rudimentary missiles from rogue states (''Experts Play Down ABM Test Failure,'' news article, July 15), perhaps we could rely for protection in the near term on their being even more faulty than the initial tests have shown our interceptors to be.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>So long as we are threatened by only a few rudimentary missiles from rogue states (''Experts Play Down ABM Test Failure,'' news article, July 15), perhaps we could rely for protection in the near term on their being even more faulty than the initial tests have shown our interceptors to be.</p>
        <p>STEPHEN W. WORREL  Falls Church, Va., July 15, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is a former Foreign Service Officer.</p>
      </block>
